to build Docker image from this docker file 
1. download all files
2. put them all in the same directory
3. use this commad in your terminal to go to the files path "cd /path-to-your-directory"
4. use this command to build the image   "docker build -t <image-name> ."
5. use this command to make a new container usng the image you build "docker run -it --name <container-name> <image-name>"
6. you will find all things set and installed 
7. event-handlers path "/sysrepo/examples"
8. xml files path "/tmp"
9. both example-module and oven plugins installed 
10. event handlers for both are ready for running directly 
11. "passwd root" this command is for setting the user for netopeer2 client connection
12. "netstat -tulnp | grep 830" check if SSH (or Netopeer2) is listening on port 830